<article>
    <h1>Global coro&#xAD;n&#xAD;avirus cases cross 50 mil&#xAD;lion fol&#xAD;low&#xAD;ing 30-day surge</h1>
    <h2>US the first na&#xAD;tion to re&#xAD;port over 100,000 daily in&#xAD;fec&#xAD;tions; Europe is worst-af&#xAD;fected re&#xAD;gion</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201109/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-09"><time>2020-11-09</time></a>
        - <span>THE BIG STORY</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>NEW YORK • Global coro­n­avirus in­fec­tions ex­ceeded 50 mil­lion yes­ter­day, ac­cord­ing to a Reuters tally, with a sec­ond wave of the virus in the past 30 days ac­count­ing for a quar­ter of the to­tal.</p>
    <p>Oc­to­ber was the worst month for the pan­demic so far, with the United States be­com­ing the first coun­try to re­port more than 100,000 daily cases. A surge in Europe con­trib­uted to the rise.</p>
    <p>The lat­est seven-day av­er­age shows global daily in­fec­tions are ris­ing by more than 540,000.</p>
    <p>More than 1.25 mil­lion peo­ple have died from the Covid-19 dis­ease that emerged in China late last year.</p>
    <p>The pan­demic’s re­cent ac­cel­er­a­tion has been fe­ro­cious.</p>
    <p>It took 32 days for the num­ber of cases to rise from 30 mil­lion to 40 mil­lion. It took just 21 days to add an­other 10 mil­lion.</p>
    <p>Europe, with about 12 mil­lion cases, is the worst-af­fected re­gion, over­tak­ing Latin Amer­ica.</p>
    <p>Europe ac­counts for 24 per cent of Covid-19 deaths.</p>
    <p>The re­gion is log­ging about one mil­lion new in­fec­tions ev­ery three days or so, ac­cord­ing to a Reuters anal­y­sis. That is 51 per cent of the global to­tal. France is record­ing 54,440 cases a day on the lat­est seven-day av­er­age, a higher rate than that in In­dia, which has a far big­ger pop­u­la­tion.</p>
    <p>The US, with about 20 per cent of global cases, is fac­ing its worst surge, record­ing more than 100,000 daily coro­n­avirus cases on the lat­est seven-day av­er­age, Reuters data showed. It re­ported a record of more than 130,000 cases on Satur­day.</p>
    <p>The lat­est US surge co­in­cided with the last month of pres­i­den­tial election cam­paign­ing.</p>
    <p>Pres­i­dent Don­ald Trump’s ral­lies, some open-air and with few masks and lit­tle so­cial dis­tanc­ing, led to 30,000 ad­di­tional con­firmed cases and likely led to more than 700 deaths, Stan­ford University econ­o­mists es­ti­mated in a re­search pa­per.</p>
    <p>In Asia, In­dia has the world’s sec­ond-high­est caseload but there has been a steady slow­down since Septem­ber, de­spite the start of the Hindu fes­ti­val sea­son.</p>
    <p>To­tal cases ex­ceeded 8.5 mil­lion last Fri­day and the daily av­er­age is 46,200, ac­cord­ing to Reuters data.</p>

